        Statutory Declarations When Selling Property in Queensland
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        A statutory declaration is a legal document with real consequences if made falsely. Here is when Queensland sellers are required to make one, who can witness it, and the mistake that makes a declaration invalid before you even start.
      </p>
    </div>
